TRE is performed if the function returnsvoid, if the return returns the result returned by the call, or if the functionreturns a run-time constant on all exits from the function. It is possible, thoughunlikely, that the return returns something else (like constant 0), and can stillbe TREâ€™d. It can be TREâ€™d if all other return instructions in the function returnthe exact same value. 4. If it can prove that callees do not access their callerstack frame, they are marked as eligible for tail call elimination (by the codegenerator).
